## 4. Reference Data Tables (Geographic Adjustments & Rates)

The system utilizes several pre-defined reference tables, either as hardcoded arrays in COBOL Copybooks or as external flat files, to define historical geographic wage indexes and base payment rates.

*   [ESCOM151](file:///Users/rohitkelapure/Downloads/ESRDCY212MainframePricerReleaseFiles/ESCOM151): Composite CBSA Wage Record. Contains hardcoded CBSA values mapping to Wage Index multipliers for Calendar Years 2006 through 2013.
*   [ESBUN210](file:///Users/rohitkelapure/Downloads/ESRDCY212MainframePricerReleaseFiles/ESBUN210): Bundled CBSA Wage Index. Contains hardcoded CBSA values mapping to Wage Index multipliers for the fully implemented bundled payment years (2011 and later).
*   [ESWRT151](file:///Users/rohitkelapure/Downloads/ESRDCY212MainframePricerReleaseFiles/ESWRT151): MSA Wage-Adjusted Rates. Maps older Metropolitan Statistical Area (MSA) codes to their historical rates.
*   [BASECBSA](file:///Users/rohitkelapure/Downloads/ESRDCY212MainframePricerReleaseFiles/BASECBSA) & [BUNDCBSA](file:///Users/rohitkelapure/Downloads/ESRDCY212MainframePricerReleaseFiles/BUNDCBSA): Flat-file representations of the CBSA data arrays.
*   [BASERATE](file:///Users/rohitkelapure/Downloads/ESRDCY212MainframePricerReleaseFiles/BASERATE): Flat file containing the National Base Payment Rate by year.
*   [ESCHI151](file:///Users/rohitkelapure/Downloads/ESRDCY212MainframePricerReleaseFiles/ESCHI151): **Special Children's Wage Index.** A customized, hardcoded override array strictly containing exactly 6 specific Provider OSCAR Numbers for Children's Hospitals (e.g. `093300`, `263302`) that trigger a specialized Wage Index overriding standard geographic calculations.

